<br>
Ok, back to my point.  Pick up groups evolve constantly.  Here's an example.  I'm at CT planks with pick-up group member a,b,c,d, and e.  Over time, someone from my guild replaces group member a.  Then group member B has to leave.  YAY!! Come on down, guild member b.  Pretty soon, the majority of the group is composed of my friends and guild mates! YAAAAY, by the way, cuz pick up groups really DO suck.  Does that now mean that because the majority of the group is composed of my friends and guildmates, that group member e no longer has rights to loot should it drop?  Nope.  Least not in my book. <br>
<br>
Or scenario B:  Me and 4 guild mates head on down to UP (or any other zone) to get some xp, but we need one more (saaaay, a cleric) and we PICK UP a cleric at zone that's LFG, how fair is it of me to not allow that cleric to have a chance at a drop after they've contributed to my day of fun and xp??  Not really very fair. <br>
<br>
When this group of 5 people decided to pick up (yes, PICK UP) another member, they were obligated to TELL him if X loot drops, so and so needs it, buzz off if that's not okay with you, otherwise since they PICKED UP another member, in all fairness, he/she should be included in any loot that drops.  <br>
<br>
Didn't say ya weren't nice, Anna, just that your pick up group philosophy was a lil lopsided.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
